A 42-year-old man died when a state vehicle transporting a group of immigrants from Limpopo to Gauteng s Lindela Repatriation Centre overturned along the N1 near Makhado on Wednesday. Police spokesman Lieutenant Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said a case of culpable homicide was opened. The Department of Home Affairs vehicle was transporting seven immigrants from Musina to Lindela in Gauteng when it allegedly got a puncture, lost control and overturned killing one immigrant aged 42 years old instantly. Others sustained serious injuries including two department officials, Ngoepe said. Lindela in western Johannesburg is a detention centre for undocumented migrants. African News Agency (ANA)